Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them into a #low sided wide baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}(drizzle), then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer and set aside. Halve the @halloumi{250%g} as if you were making 2 'steaks', then chop each half into 5 'baton' shaped pieces. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and thinly slice. Pick the @mint{1}/2%bunch leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Add the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} to a #bowl{} along with the @tahini{22%g} and the @honey{15%g}. Squeeze in the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Gradually stir through the @water for the batter{150%ml} (see ingredients for amount) with a #fork{} until well combined. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Quarter the @pomegranate{1/2}. Holding the pomegranate pieces over a bowl of water, scoop out the seeds into the bowl of water. > Use a fork to do this, it helps to release the seeds. Remove the seeds from the water set aside. Discard the white pith.

Pop the @falafel mix{150%g} into a #medium mixing bowl{} and add the @chermoula spice mix{1} and lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper and add the @water{150%ml}. Mix together until well combined then set aside for ~{3-4%minutes} (the mixture will thicken in this time). Meanwhile, roast the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Once the falafel mixture has thickened, shape into balls (4 per person). > Wet your hands before shaping the falafels to prevent them from sticking to your hands. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the falafels and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Pop onto a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until firm and cooked through ~{6-8%minutes}. Remove from the oven.

Pop your pan back on medium-high heat and add a drizzle of oil. While the oil is heating up, pop the @plain flour{8%g} in a #shallow bowl{} and add half the @sumac{1}. Mix together, then add the halloumi fries to the bowl and toss to coat in the flour. Lay the halloumi fries in your hot oil and fry until golden all over, ~{6-7%minutes} total. Remove the pan from the heat. Meanwhile, pop your @Greek style flatbreads{4} on the top shelf of the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve the flatbreads on large #plates{} (2 per person). Spread a spoonful of your dressing on the bottom of each flatbread, add the potatoes, baby gem and falafels. Serve the halloumi fries alongside, then drizzle over the remaining dressing and sprinkle over the pomegranate seeds, mint and remaining sumac. Enjoy!